    <stitle>5 SPEED AND 6 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON SERIES - INSTALL - REVERSE IDLER GEAR ASSEMBLY (FS-5306/6306)
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="4">
        <title>REVERSE IDLER GEAR ASSEMBLY (FS-5306/6306)</title>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>The reverse idler can be assembled in either the vertical or horizontal case position.</para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Lubricate the idler shaft with oil before assembly. Refer to GROUP 10 - LUBRICATION in the
                    CTS-5000 Master Service Manual for recommended lubes.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Insert the spacer in the reverse idler gear (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13026g5">Figure 165</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13026g5" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13026g5" filename="../figg13/G13026g5.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 165. Insert Spacer in Reverse Idler Gear and Install Bearings</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the bearings on either side of the reverse idler spacer (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13026g5">Figure 165</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use grease on the reverse idler thrust washers to hold in place (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13026g6">Figure 166</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13026g6" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13026g6" filename="../figg13/G13026g6.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 166. Position Washer Tangs and Install Reverse Idler Assembly</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Position washer tangs to align the housing grooves (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13026g6">Figure 166</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the reverse idler assembly in the housing (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13026g6">Figure 166</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Insert the idler shaft into the case bore and line up the shaft notch with the case notch (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13026g7">Figure 167</hotlnk>). Do not install the shaft all the way.
            </para>
            <figure id="f13026g7" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13026g7" filename="../figg13/G13026g7.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 167. Insert Idler Shaft into Case Bore</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the locating ball (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13026g8">Figure 168</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13026g8" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13026g8" filename="../figg13/G13026g8.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 168. Install Locating Ball and Drive Shaft into Position</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Drive the shaft into position (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13026g8">Figure 168</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
